description:
If a non-decoding error is encountered on the last result of a cursor iteration, any for loop iterating over it will continue endlessly with all the results being LogicError's indicating that advancing a failed cursor is an error. We should ensure that nil has been returned at least once before returning such an error to ensure this doesnt happen.

repro with a collection with 2 documents in it:
{code}        
let client = try MongoClient.makeTestClient()
let cursor = try client.db("woo").collection("woo").find([:], options: FindOptions(batchSize: 1))
let fp = FailPoint.failCommand(failCommands: ["getMore"], mode: .alwaysOn, errorCode: 10)
try fp.enable()
for result in cursor {
    print(result)
}
// .document()
// .failure(errorCode 10)
// .failure(LogicError)
// .failure(LogicError)
// ..

{code}

In {{findOne}}, we ensure we only kill the cursor after a successful document retrieval since we assume the cursor will clean itself up appropriately after encountering an error. Cursors do not close themselves after encountering \{{DecodingError}} s, however, and in those cases we leak the cursor.
{code}struct Blah: Decodable {
    let lfkjadsjkla: String
}
let coll = db.collection("blah", withType: Blah.self)
try coll.findOne([:]).wait()
{code}
yields (in Debug mode)
{code}Assertion failed: cursor or change stream wasn't closed before it went out of scope: file /home/patrick/mongo-swift-driver/Sources/MongoSwift/CursorCommon.swift, line 247
{code}

{{equalsIgnoreKeyOrder}}, which compares two documents for equality without considering order of the keys, currently ensures documents contained in arrays have the same key order, while not ensuring regular subdocuments have the same key order. This should be fixed so that documents contained in arrays are compared without considering key order too.
{code:java}
// this should be true but is currently false
["x": [["a": 1, "b": 2]]].equalsIgnoreKeyOrder(["x": [["b": 2, "a": 1]]]){code}

